Kaveel Singh, News24A paraglider was rescued from Porterville after hanging off the side of the mountain for hours on end. (Supplied, Johan Marais - Wilderness Search and Rescue ) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; An almost seven-hour rescue operation saved the life of a paraglider near Porterville, in the Western Cape, on Tuesday. The paraglider had been hanging off the side of the mountain since 14:30 on Tuesday. He was rescued around 21:30, Wilderness Search and Rescue spokesperson Johann Marais said. Paramedics and technical rescuers were taken to the scene. They put the man on a drip and stabilised him.&nbsp;An SAAF Oryx helicopter was used in the rescue.The man would be flown to Air Force Base Ysterplaat and taken to hospital via ambulance.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.